{"name":"Clues from  the Crowds","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>It is often difficult to extract information from groups such as hive gangs or Administratum scribes, as often numbers can bolster recalcitrance to questioning. A veteran Acolyte knows that such groups can hold critical information to complete an investigation, and can throw more effective nets when interrogating groups and reveal valued clues. Once per day, he can re-roll a test made to gather information from a group of people.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 30","aptitudes":"General, Social","benefit":"Can re-roll a test made to gather information from  a group.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3J8DkDSWILY0JNBa"}
{"name":"Jaded","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s wide travels have shown him both wonders and horrors beyond the ken of most. The galaxy has thrown its worst at him and he has yet to flinch. Mundane events, from death&rsquo;s horrific visage to xenos abominations, do not force him to gain Insanity points or make Fear tests. Daemons, Warp manifestations, and other unnatural effects still affect him normally.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Ignore mundane horrors.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3M03O3gstWuVxjnj"}
{"name":"Warp Sense","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s senses have evolved to perceive the Warp in parallel with the physical world. The character can use the Psyniscience Skill as a Free Action instead of as a Half Action. He can also passively detect psychic effects and entities without the need to actively seek them out. Whenever the character could detect such a Warp signature or a creature, the GM can allow him to make a Psyniscience skill test to detect it, in the same way he could use Awareness to spot an ambush without knowing it is there.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Perception 30, Psy rating, Psyniscience","aptitudes":"Perception, Psyker","benefit":"Allows Psyniscience test as Free Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3XPYfs1c4txlY6Tv"}
{"name":"Takedown","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>When making a Standard Attack or Charge action, the Acolyte can declare that he is attempting a takedown his target. He then rolls to hit (using his Weapon Skill) as normal, applying all the regular modifiers for the attack action. If the character hits and would have done at least 1 point of damage (after reduction for Armour and Toughness), no wounds are caused. Instead, the opponent must make a Challenging (+0) Toughness test or be Stunned for 1 Round and knocked Prone. In addition, when performing a Stun Action, the character does not suffer the normal &ndash;20 penalty to his Weapon Skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"Make special attack to stun opponent.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3Zlm0PDDbzY1DUCJ"}
{"_id":"40REQCKg0KSnk5rf","name":"Ambidextrous","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>This talent does not represent true ambidexterity so much as sufficient training with both hands to make the distinction moot. When combined with Two-Weapon Wielder talent, the penalty for making attacks with both weapons in the same turn drops to &ndash;10.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ag 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Balistic Skill","benefit":"Reduce penalties for using two weapons.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/1.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Blinding Fight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Years of practice and development of his other senses allows the Acolyte to fight in close combat without the benefit of sight. He ignores all penalties for fighting with a melee weapon while suffering from obscured vision, permitting him to fight in fog, smoke, or darkness more effectively. See page 229 for a full list of normal penalties based on lighting and vision. Note this talent only improves his chances to hit with melee weapons, and has no effect on ranged weapon attacks.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Perception 30","aptitudes":"Perception, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Eliminates melee combat penalties for obscured vision.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4anPGko7d8QdgDg2"}
{"name":"Ferric Summons","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained himself in better use of his Ferric Lure Implants (see page 182). He can summon to his hand an unsecured metal object weighing up to 2 kilograms per point of his Willpower bonus, and can summon such objects up to 40 metres distant.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ferric Lure Implants, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Willpower, Tech","benefit":"Can summon larger metallic objects.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6ZkPOKTWOdlou4D4"}
{"name":"Keen Intuition","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained extensively to notice objects that seem out of place or hidden. This can bring the smallest irregularity to prominence, revealing the heresy festering beneath the surface. After failing an Awareness skill test, the character can re-roll the test with a &ndash;10 modifier.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Perception, Social","benefit":"Can retry Awareness test once with â€“10 modifier.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HP2TAbiAQQkIDIIG"}
{"name":"Technical Knock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Either through the ease of long practice, or the proper ritual to appease a weapon&rsquo;s machine spirit, the Acolyte can clear stoppages with a simple knock or solid smack of his hand to a weapon. Once per round, he may attempt to unjam a gun (see page 224) as a Half Action rather than a Full Action. He must touch the weapon to make use of this talent.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 30","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Un-jam gun as Half Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JKfuUaglyKxfD0RG"}
{"name":"Mounted Warrior*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Specialisations: Melee, Ranged</p>\n<p>Hard-won experience fighting from the saddle or seat of a vehicle has trained the Acolyte to adjust for the motion of mounted combat, moving with the vehicle instead of fighting against it. When a character purchases this talent, he selects the specialisation that matches the characteristic prerequisite and aptitude used in purchase. He then reduces any penalty for making corresponding attacks (Melee or Ranged) from a moving vehicle or mount by 10 for each time the talent has been purchased in that specialisation. This applies to both ordinary attack actions and vehicle combat actions, such as Hit and Run.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 (Trained) in any Operate skill or Rank 2 (Trained) in Survival skill, Ballistic Skill 30 or Weapon Skill 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill, Ofence","benefit":"No penalty for mounted fighting","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JU0Nt6SkvbWk19PD"}
{"name":"Flagellant","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows that pain is cleansing, and regularly mortifies his own flesh to atone for his sins. As a Full Action, the character can inlict some suitable punishment on his own body, sufering 1d5&ndash;2 levels of Fatigue (to a minimum of 1). He then gains a +10 bonus on Willpower tests to resist Fear, Pinning, psychic powers, or sufering Corruption, for one hour or until the end of the current encounter. If the Acolyte also possesses the Frenzy talent, he can enter a Frenzied state as a Free Action while under the effects of this talent.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 30","aptitudes":"Ofence, Toughness","benefit":"gain stat boni for fatigue","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JXEJX6mPRtjObIvY"}
{"name":"Disarm","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte can wrest weapons from his opponents&rsquo; hands through practised technique or brute force. As a Full Action, the character may make an Opposed Weapon Skill test against one target with whom he is engaged. If the Acolyte wins the test, the enemy drops his weapon to the ground. Should the Acolyte score three or more degrees of success, he can take the enemy&rsquo;s weapon from him.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Defence","benefit":"Force opponent to drop weapon.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"L7MaaEvMFhBEU1sa"}
{"name":"Enemy*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Any listed in the sidebar The Powers of Askellon above, and others at GM&rsquo;s discretion</p>\n<p>The opposite of Peer (see page 130); the Acolyte is particularly despised and possibly hunted by a specific social group or organisation, heretical cult, or xenos race. He suffers an additional &ndash;10 penalty to Fellowship and Influence tests when dealing with this group, and the GM can use them to complicate his life from time to time. Unlike other talents, Enemy does not cost any xp to purchase and cannot be taken as an advance. Instead the GM and player can agree to award it when appropriate to the adventure or campaign. It can be removed with the approval of the GM, if the character has redeemed himself with the group in question. The Enemy talent can be awarded multiple times for the same group, in which case it should be listed as Enemy (X), with X equalling the number of times the talent has been awarded. This can be used to represent groups who particularly hate the Acolyte and want to see him dead. In game terms, the penalty to Fellowship tests increases to &ndash;10 times X.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"General, Social","benefit":"An organization or group particularly despises  the character","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"L9yafFUQldUtd2JY"}
{"name":"Iron Jaw","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has taken blows from Orks and given back as good as he got, bouncing back from most strikes without ill effects. Whenever this character becomes Stunned, he may make a Challenging (+0) Toughness test as a Free Action to ignore the effects.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Toughness 40","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Test Toughness to overcome Stunning.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NeV3T5JD7zabggXX"}
{"name":"Weapon Training*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Bolt, Chain, Flame, Heavy, Las, Launcher, Melta, Plasma, Power, Low-Tech, Shock, and Solid Projectile</p>\n<p>The Acolyte can use all weapons with Class: Pistol, Basic, Melee, Throwing, and Vehicle within the group he has selected with this talent. When a character attempts to use a weapon he does not have the correct Weapon Training talent for, he suffers a &ndash;20 penalty to any relevant Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill test.</p>\n<p>The character can only use weapons with Class: Heavy without suffering the &ndash;20 penalty if he has both Weapon Training in the appropriate group and Weapon Training (Heavy). This talent can be taken more than once, each time with a different Specialisation. Note that a character without the Weapon Training (Low-Tech) talent operating a weapon that functions as a Low-Tech weapon in certain circumstances does not suffer this penalty, so long as he has the applicable Weapon Training talent for the weapon (Power for a power sword, for example).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"General, Finesse","benefit":"Use Weapon Group without penalty","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TcYLVgNRT7no9ugW"}
{"name":"Rapid Reload","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The firing ranges and weapon drill chambers are the Acolyte&rsquo;s constant abode. Hours of reloading countless magazines or power cells means that he can replace them without looking and without thinking, even in the middle of combat. He halves all reload times, rounding down. Thus, a Half Action reload becomes a Free Action, a Full Action reload becomes a Half Action, and so on.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Reduce reload time.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Wn6FDKbac8y8JUzz"}
{"name":"Catfall","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Gymnastic ability and natural balance enables the Acolyte to fall great distances without harm. He automatically reduces the effective distance of all falls by a number of metres equal to his Agility bonus, ignoring this distance as if it did not exist. He also adds +20 to his Acrobatics skill tests when using the Jump special skill use, as it pertains to reducing damage from falling.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 30","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Reduce falling damage.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"b7WyqJG90SKPL2Dr"}
{"name":"Grenadier","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows that grenades and other explosives are amongst the most effective ways to bring down marauding alien beasts, or to quickly thin out hordes of lesser xenos monstrosities. When the character misses with a thrown weapon or weapon with the Blast quality, he may reduce the distance it scatters by a number of metres up to half his BS bonus.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 35","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"reduce the scatter distance of missed throw/blast rolls","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dowWBjmSScQKLPR4"}
{"name":"Skilled Rider","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Often, the best way to overcome the heretic is with merciless speed, and so many Acolytes make extensive use of vehicles and mounts in their pursuit of humanity&rsquo;s enemies. Whether the character has used his prized bike until it feels like an extension of his own body, or he has the experience necessary to instantly adjust to the strange mounts and vehicles found across the Askellon Sector, moving to or from the saddle or pilot&rsquo;s seat is second nature. Whenever the character would be thrown from or tossed about within his vehicle, he makes an Ordinary (+10) Agility test. If he succeeds, the character may choose to either land safely on his feet or retain in his original position in the vehicle. In addition, once per round the character can attempt an Ordinary (+10) Agility test to Mount or Dismount a vehicle as a Free Action.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in any Operate skill","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"You know what you are riding and its hard to throw you off","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"e2uguHyMJXKMX4Nd"}
{"name":"Peer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Any listed in the sidebar The Powers of Askellon</p>\n<p>(see page 126), others at GM&rsquo;s discretion</p>\n<p>The Acolyte knows how to deal with a particular social group or organisation, or even xenos race. He gains a +10 bonus to all Fellowship and Influence tests when interacting with this chosen group, and at the GM&rsquo;s discretion can sometimes call upon them for favours. The GM and player may agree to award this talent when appropriate to the adventure or campaign, though the character must still pay the experience cost for the Talent as normal. This talent can be awarded multiple times for the same group, in which case it should be listed as Peer (X), with X equalling the number of times the talent has been awarded. This can be used to represent groups who particularly like the character and may even be staunch allies. In game terms, the bonus to Fellowship tests increases to +10 times X. Additionally, when the character acquires this talent, he increases his Influence by 1.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 30","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Social","benefit":"Character has good reputation amongst chosen group.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gT960Rvmyh4odckr"}
{"name":"Resistance*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Cold, Fear, Heat, Poisons, Psychic Powers, Radiation, Vacuum, Other</p>\n<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s background, experience, training, exposure, or plain stubbornness has developed a resistance within him. Each time he selects this talent, choose one area of resistance. He gains a +10 bonus when making tests to resist effects of this type. The GM can require approval for certain choices, or justification based on the Acolyte&rsquo;s past.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Gain +10 bonus to particular resistance test.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"glqJAKP6vhD1h9fr"}
{"name":"Leaping Dodge","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has become practiced at escaping weapons that cover an area to deadly effect, from flamers to strange xenos devices. When he would make an Agility test to avoid attacks from weapons with the Spray quality, he may make the test using his Dodge (Ag) skill instead.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 35, Rank 2 in the Dodge skill","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"Use dodge instead of Ag to avoid spray","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hU49ypwHIA0DFZ0c"}
{"name":"Bodyguard","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained to protect his allies or superiors, prepared to even throw himself in the way of a bolt shell or whirring chain blade if necessary.</p>\n<p>Effect: After an enemy makes a successful attack against an ally, the character may use a Reaction to move up to his Half Move distance in order to interpose himself between the attacker and target. The attack is then resolved against the character instead of the original target. In the case of a melee attack, the character may also attempt to Parry the attack as part of his Reaction.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 35","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"Take a hit for an ally","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iZfqT9jKPhhlcG3t"}
{"name":"Double Team","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has experience of fighting in paired teams that work together to take down their enemies. When Ganging Up on an opponent, he gains an additional +10 bonus to Weapon Skill tests. If both the characters that outnumber the enemy have this talent, then both gain an additional +10 bonus, for a total of +20. This bonus is in addition to the normal bonus gained from Ganging Up on an opponent (see page 229).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"General, Offence","benefit":"Gain additional +10 for outnumbering opponent.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lR3qTxoa9pdemA3t"}
{"name":"Sound Constitution","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte gains an additional wound. He can purchase this talent additional times up to twice his Toughness bonus. When he gains this talent multiple times, note the number of times it has been taken after the talent, such as Sound Constitution (3).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Toughness, General","benefit":"Gain an additional wound.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pGlsgkBCDhx8j2T9"}
{"name":"Weapon-Tech","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte calls upon the blessings of the Omnissiah, channelling his faith into his weapon and performing armament rituals to more readily smite his foes. Once per combat encounter, as a Free Action, this character may enhance any Melta, Plasma, Power, or Exotic weapon he is personally wielding. This increases the weapon&rsquo;s damage and penetration by an amount equal to the character&rsquo;s Intelligence bonus until the end of the round.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 40, Tech Use +10","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Increase potency of advanced weaponry.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qXqE7Kwr9RXtnGN0"}
{"name":"Die Hard","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Through either mental resolve or sheer stubbornness, the Acolyte refuses to fall. When this character would suffer a level of Fatigue due to the Blood Loss condition, he makes a Challenging (+0) Willpower test; if he succeeds, he does not suffer a level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Test Willpower to avoid Fatigue from Blood Loss.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ri79roijsEkUjXRF"}
{"name":"Quick Draw","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has practised so frequently with his weapons that they practically leap into his hands in response to a simple thought. As a Free Action, the character may draw and ready a Pistol or Basic weapon, or a one-handed Melee weapon.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Agility, Finesse","benefit":"Draw weapon as Free Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"w4CXKbF2pMeeegU6"}
{"name":"Frenzy","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s temper and passion boil just below the surface of his psyche, mostly held in check by his rational mind, but easily released when needed. If he spends one full round fuelling his anger&mdash;by flagellation, drugs, or other means&mdash;on the next round, he goes into an uncontrolled rage, gaining a +10 bonus to Weapon Skill, Strength, Toughness, and Willpower, but suffering a &ndash; 0 penalty to Ballistic Skill, Intelligence, and Fellowship. Note that characteristic penalties are different from characteristic damage (see page 188), and cannot reduce a characteristic below 1. While Frenzied, the character must attack the nearest enemy in melee combat if possible. If he is not engaged with the nearest enemy, he must move towards that enemy and engage it if possible. He will not take obviously suicidal actions such as leaping off a building in order to engage someone on the ground, but he will take any actions that offer a reasonable opportunity to engage in melee with the nearest enemy.</p>\n<p>While Frenzied, he is immune to Fear, Pinning, Stunning effects, and the effects of Fatigue; he cannot Parry, retreat, or flee. He remains Frenzied for the duration of the combat, and cannot use psychic powers while Frenzied. After combat ends, or if there are no more eligible enemy targets for the character to attack, he can make a Willpower test to snap out of his Frenzy. If he fails, he must continue to attack, favouring NPCs over PCs. Each successive round, however, he can make another Willpower test, with a cumulative +10 bonus to return to a stable state of mind and come out of Frenzy. After Frenzying, he cannot Frenzy again for at least an hour, as he recovers his mental and physical strength.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Enter psychotic rage to gain combat bonuses.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"x3DdT7r5CPXFN56L"}
{"name":"Leap Up","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>A combination of athletic ability and speed allows the Acolyte to spring to his feet in virtually any circumstance. He can stand up as a Free Action.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 30","aptitudes":"Agility, General","benefit":"Stand as a Free Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ybLe4NzsPBm8enbj"}
{"name":"Nowhere to Hid","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s keen eye ensures he can spot soft points even in the most impregnable of protective cover. When he damages cover (see page 229), the character adds his degrees of success from the attack to the reduction of the cover&rsquo;s Armour value. If using a weapon that does not require a skill test, he adds 1 instead.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Perception 30","aptitudes":"Perception, Offence","benefit":"Can add DoS from the attack to reduce armour value  of cover.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/1.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yvHWw0helIyUWVkJ"}
